4.10	Friendship,_Pittsburgh	Friendship (Pittsburgh)	Friendship is a neighborhood of large Victorian houses in the East End of the City of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States, about four miles (6 km) east of Pittsburgh's Golden Triangle. Friendship is bordered on the north by Garfield (at Penn Avenue), on the east by East Liberty (at Negley Avenue), on the south by Shadyside (at Centre Avenue), and on the west by Bloomfield (at South Graham Street). It is divided into 3 Pittsburgh City Council districts, District 7 Patrick Dowd, District 8 Bill Peduto and District 9 Rev. Ricky Burgess.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Pgh_locator_friendship.svg/300px-Pgh_locator_friendship.svg.png
